  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acute gastroenteritis is a common cause of hospital admission and health office visits and
      have a huge burden on the economy of developing countries. The investigators proposed this
      observational prospective study during summer period in a community and tertiary care
      hospital in a rural area of Lebanon to investigate the etiologies and age distribution of
      admitted cases to general pediatric floor from the age of 1 month up to the age of 14 years.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
